{\rm Binomial}(4,0.5)
\begin{align*} p_0 = \Pr[S = 0] &= \sum_{k=0}^2 \binom{4}{k} (0.5)^k (0.5)^{4-k} = \frac{11}{16}, \\ p_1 = \Pr[S = 0.5] &= \binom{4}{3} (0.5)^3 (0.5)^1 = \frac{1}{4}, \\ p_2 = \Pr[S = 1] &= \binom{4}{4} (0.5)^4 (0.5)^0 = \frac{1}{16}. \end{align*} 
